    "remark": "Insight: relative error is dimensionless; absolute error carries the unit of the quantity. They are linked by $\\Delta A=\\left(\\Delta A/A\\right)\\cdot A$, and the bridge factor here is the whole area $A\\approx314$ cm$^2$ — not $100$. For a power law $A\\propto r^n$ the relative errors scale by $n$ ($\\Delta A/A=n\\,\\Delta r/r$), here $n=2$. Reporting a percentage as if it were the physical error is among the most common — and most expensive — laboratory blunders."
